		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.visual6502.org/images/pages/Nintendo_3193A.html">http://www.visual6502.org/images/pages/ ... 3193A.html</a><!-- m --><br />is the best I know of.<br /><br />I think &quot;figuring out which microcontroller it was given the research abilities of 1986&quot; is actually the biggest block. <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://hackmii.com/2010/01/the-weird-and-wonderful-cic/">http://hackmii.com/2010/01/the-weird-and-wonderful-cic/</a><!-- m --><br />Segher's work is a pretty good illustration of what they would have had to do, given just the raw readout of the internal ROM.

		

